So this map is some were around par level. I though I'd explain it a little so while looking though the request I stumbled upon this...
Posted by Kurosaki08 I would like a map made for my realism unit. I would like it to be some sort of Army Boot Camp map. With barracks, m4a1 range, sniper range, able to run obstacle course, buildings to clear, and some sort of large platform with a stage or podium (this will be where my companies fall into formation). I would really appreciate if this could be done for me. Thanks in advance!
So I started working on this however then California caught on fire and I found out I get dispatched in 8 hours so I might not be back for some time so I thought I'd give Kurosaki08 his map. The textured is a little rushed and the lighting doesn't have sources but nothings missing that will affect game play. I may come back to this latter but for now it's as done as it's going to get. When playing this map it really only works for an organized clan or group since the spawns are a little close. The armory has 10 of every gun in the game. It may cause lag if you throw them all in to the center of the room. Other things to note about the armory is the weapons are a little close together so you don't always get the one you want. Outside there is a shooting range with targets at 50, 100 and 150 feet. Their small targets so you'll find out how bad a shot you really are. Next to the range there is an obstacle course. It goes like this run, crawl, jump, climb, balance, cross over to the other side, jump to water, swim, run and shoot. My best time was 28 seconds with a p90. If you using this to test people you can come up with rules like every shot is plus one second or the shotgun is plus 10 seconds since the shooting portion requires you to shoot small targets to progress. On the other side of the barracks/armory there is a yard with several basic structures for Kurosaki08 to practice clearing rooms. And lastly and my favorite there is a stage behind the barracks with a giant American flag behind it for giving dramatic speeches to clan members. The flag can be turned off via button on the podium for all you European/Canadian(/ where ever you are) people out there. I would have used a UN flag but due to time constraints and it not being easy to do with out importing a texture I choose to just go with an American flag. ==UPDATE:May 22 2009 I'm back again. I was looking over the comments and decided to add more stuff. now there is a target wall behind each of the shooting stall targets. I is not interactive like the old targets but the old ones are still there. also i added a full house with targets to the training yard. all of the houses have targets now and about half of them light up when hit. Due to technical limitations with hammer i can only have a few of the targets that light up so don't bother asking unless you have an idea for a work around. Near the entrance i added a tower with a over view of the house where the dots represent targets and they toggle on or off when hit. i played around with triggers to see if i could get it to only turn off when hit instead of toggling but with toggle as the only option it is sort of hard. you still some times get the wrong gun in the armory (Almost always) the only way to fix this is to make the armory far to big.

Training_Aim by Katas [ESP] An individual map for powering your aim! UPDATED TO TRAINING_AIM3, GET IT NOW!! I created this map for training my aim and I decided to show it the world :D. It has a Control panel for setting the intervals in wich targets and respawned and holded randomly in the wall. You can choose all the weapons from Counter-Strike: Source to practise with. Use this map everyday for aiming better ingame :). It is not necesary to reload weapons while shooting the targets (unlimited ammo).
Features >> You can control the respawn and holding delay of targets. >> Explanations about Control panel in the wall (decals). People with low textures setting or FPS configurations won't be able to see those explanations. >> You can choose any weapon from CS:S. >> Hits Counter that counts how much targets did you shoot. >> A beep sounds when you get to shoot at a target. >> You can control how much targets to spawn in a row before stopping (25/50/100/999). >> Different distances from the wall (levels) >> Start and Stop button in each level. >> 200 Different targets all over the wall. >> Unlimited ammo with all the weapons (Don't need to reload). >> It has a good environment to prevent headaches (xD). >> Custom textures for the buttons.
How to use: Open CS:S, create a server and select training_aim in the maps list (don't allow bots). Join a team, choose a weapon, set the delay and duration you prefer for targets and go the level you want. Then click start button and wait 2 seconds for the first target to appear, you can practise moving left and right or being stand in a position. If you liked it please Vote and Comment :)

Map made on request: Plz make sniper target practice map Target Practice map with moving targets, made for training. Designed for single player, but it is possible to run the map on a server, if mp_limitteams is set to 0. Designed for sniper practice, because the targets are a 1 hit kill, but you can also train with an ak47/m4a1/deagle. Map devided in 7 sections, when you have killed all the targets of 1 section you get 15 seconds to move on before the door closes. I tried to improve the movement of the car in section 7 so it would look more realistic, but for some reason the car kept spawning to the wrong direction(0 270 0), therefor I was forced to check the flag 'Fixed orientation'. If someone knows how to fix this please comment/pm me. Map is not protected from decompiling, because I would like other people to learn from this map, I would like to see other (training) maps with moving targets/parts. PM me if you have any questions. Type this in console to refill your ammo: sv_cheats 1 impulse 101 Please comment and assess. - Black Credits: - Valve - PrivateParts

_sText:
"If you're not careful and you noclip out of reality in the wrong areas, you end up in the Backrooms, where it's nothing but the stink of old moist carpet, the madness of mono-yellow, the endless background noise of fluorescent lights at maximum hum-buzz, and approximately six hundred million square miles of randomly segmented empty rooms to be trapped in. God save you if you hear something wandering around nearby because it sure as hell heard you."

This map is a recreation of the Backrooms for CSS. It isn't really meant for playing matches in but it is good if you're going to use it for Garry's Mod. I tried to go the authentic yellow wallpaper look which I've not seen many people do when it comes to recreating the Backrooms in the Source engine. I hope you enjoy it.Â It's inspired by a YouTube video called "INTO THE BACKROOMS" by Evan Royalty

This is an improvement of my previous map "tex_dodget_knives". This map uses HDR lighting and has a better water texture, as well as stripping you of your weapons and only giving you a knife and a he grenade at the start of each round. Definately an improvement. Enjoy.

IMPROVED -- IMPROVED

The water on the ground hurts you but the body of water in the middle of the map is safe to swim down and there (if u bothered to read this you deserve to know) lies a scout that falls from the top of the map. If you pay attention at the beginning of each round you will see it splash into the water at the top.

A lighthouse structure stands in a corner with the sun behind it throwing a light shadow over the map. There is a body of water thinly spread over the ground taking up the majority of the ground, but there is a dock like system to manoevre around it. The boxes and other obstacles make this a fun and strategic map to play on.
